 1995</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> (organic chemistry)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:11.25pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Career within the Pharmaceutical Industry 1995-2002</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:11.25pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Career break to bring up children 2002-2013</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:11.25pt; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Appointed Daphne Jackson Fellow 1/7/2013 at the University of Huddersfield</span></li></ul><p style="line-height:11.25pt; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:11.25pt; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">After a significant career break to bring up three children I anticipated that it would be unlikely I could secure a new position</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> wit</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">hin the chemical industry which would be both flexible enough to fit with my family, but also at </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a similar level</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> which</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> I had previously achieved. However, whilst considering my options I became aware of the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Daphne Jackson Trust</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, which aims to help </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">scientists return to their careers following a break, at an appropriate level, and with flexible part-time working.</span></p><p style="line-height:11.25pt; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">After investigating this enormously valuable opportunity more fully, I approached Huddersfield University as a potential host, and submit</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ted a full application. After submitting a peer reviewed proposal and interview,   I was delighted to be appointed a Daphne Jackson Research Fellow earlier this year. The Trust secured funding on my behalf, partly from the University of Hu</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ddersfield, and p</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">artly from</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> EPS</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">RC.</span></p><p style="line-height:11.25pt; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">I would like to submit evidence to this Government </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">inquiry into women in STEM careers because I want to emphasise how valuable the Daphne Jackson Trust has been to me. Without this opportunity, it would have been highly unlikely I </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">would have returned to a career i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">cience, partly because of the decline in the Pharmaceutical Industry of late</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> (and thus the number of positions for chemists has reduced significantly)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, and partly because after such a long career break I would not be con</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">fident of applying for a position for which I am qualified. In addition, the flexibility in working and part time hours</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">means that I can fit my career around my personal life. Fellows are given support in their return to work, in the form of (re)- training</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> courses, and by being given a mentor. The position is for two years and I am confident that on completion of the Fellowship I will be in a position to return to my STEM career.</span></p><p style="line-height:11.25pt; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">September 2013</span></p><p style="line-height:11.25pt; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:11.25pt; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;